<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-365-672  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 365 672.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  April 1990 v111 n4 p41(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Accessing information is a growing global asset. (on-lineretrieval)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mortensen, Erik.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Quick, accurate on-line information retrieval systems will have acentral role in the efficient, automated office of the future.andO;End users are becoming more sophisticated in the specificity oftheir needs, and are looking to local area networks and multiplevendors to resolve their information technology andtelecommunication problems.andP;  On-line information retrievalcombines mainframe database and telecommunications technologies.andO;There are a number of information system vendors to choose from,depending on the information required.andP;  Vendors includeCompuServe, Dow Jones/News Retrieval, The Source, Pergamon ORBITInfoLine, DIALOG Information Services Inc. and Mead Data CentralInc. These services provide analysis of companies, stock marketsummaries and other types of information.andP;  On-line informationretrieval may prove a necessity for all automated offices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Office AutomationInformation Storage and RetrievalLocal Area NetworksElectronic PublishingOffice ProceduresOn-LineInformation UtilitiesTelecommunicationsInformation services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>